      <item>
        <title>redis shutdown issues</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;when using redis servers with password authentication you may experience problems with shutting down server.
it took sometimes up to 5 minutes to shut down server until i foudn out that redis was the problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the solution si simple: edit the /etc/init.d/redis_6379  file to “stop” section&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;add -a “yourredispassword”&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-console&quot; data-lang=&quot;console&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;go&quot;&gt;CLIEXEC -p $REDISPORT shutdown&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;then your redis service will shutdown quickly&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
