      <item>
        <title>manage postgres backups with jenkins</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;with jenkins you can use it also for backing up your postgres database scheduled with cron.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i assume you have jenkins user in system.
login as user postgres and go to psql console:
create user jenkins in psql:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-sql&quot; data-lang=&quot;sql&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;create&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;user&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;jenkins&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;now we need to grant permissions for this user:&lt;/p&gt;

